ARTICLE.TITLE: West Kentucky Star
ARTICLE.TEXT:
Bill to End Robocalls Passes

By West Kentucky Star Staff

UNION CITY - Tennessee 8th District Congressman David Kustoff, (R-Germantown), has announced the passage of the TRACED Act.Congressman Kustoff told KYTN that he introduced the bill on the House Floor on Wednesday.He explained that after working with colleagues in both the House and Senate, the two chambers produced compromised legislation to prevent the harassing robocall scams most Americans receive.Following the passage, Congressman Kustoff said he looks forward to President Trump signing the bill into law.
